--- G Ramasubramani &lt;grama@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;         In this case however, it is a user defined exception and
&gt; hence I know what message to expect. What would be a proper course of
&gt; action in case it is a system level exception?


Here&#39;s what I do:

  try {
    objectUnderTest.failMethod();
    fail(&quot;failMethod call did not get exception&quot;);
  }
  catch (ExpectedException e) {
    // Nothing, all is well
    // If e has instance data, might check it
  }
  // Catch any unexpected checked exceptions and fail()

I like fail() better than assert(false) since it expresses intent.

I don&#39;t bother to check the message of the exception since the class is
usually enough and the message is potentially unstable in the presence
of changes elsewhere. However, if the exception contains other data I
might check that. A notable example: for RemoteException I would
probably at least check the type of the detail.

